oc:kn_09998d14 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When applying GPU acceleration hints" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Using `will-change` excessively creates new compositor layers that consume significant GPU memory and can actually hurt performance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each layer consumes memory and compositing many layers increases GPU overhead. `will-change` should be used sparingly only for elements that are about to be animated." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_22e4b6f7 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing Core Web Vitals metrics" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Core Web Vitals thresholds must be met: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms / INP < 200ms, CLS < 0.1. Reserve explicit dimensions or aspect-ratio for images, videos, and embeds to prevent layout shifts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are Google's user experience benchmarks that directly impact search ranking and user perception of quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2e40d0a9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After applying optimizations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Compare before/after Lighthouse scores, test on low-end devices, throttle to 3G, verify no functionality regressions, and confirm the experience feels faster." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without verification, optimizations may have no real impact or may have introduced subtle regressions that aren't immediately obvious." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_53acb163 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any optimization work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never optimize without measuring first. Always establish baseline metrics before making changes and compare after." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature optimization wastes time on things that don't matter and can introduce bugs without measurable benefit." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_714a53a0 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When verifying performance improvements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Measure on real devices with real network conditions. Desktop Chrome with a fast connection is not representative of the actual user experience." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most users are on mobile devices with slower CPUs and network connections. Testing only on developer machines gives a false sense of performance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9586d828 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When applying any optimization technique" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never sacrifice accessibility for performance gains, break existing functionality, or lazy load above-fold content." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Performance gains that break usability or accessibility create a worse overall user experience than the original performance issue." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a00c54c5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When approaching any performance optimization task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow a systematic strategy: measure → identify bottleneck → optimize loading (images, JS, CSS, fonts, loading strategy) → optimize rendering (layout, paint, composite) → optimize animations → optimize network → verify improvements." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A structured approach ensures comprehensive coverage and prevents skipping critical areas like network optimization or rendering pipeline issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_dabb4664 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prioritizing which performance issues to tackle" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Optimize the biggest bottleneck first. Don't waste time on micro-optimizations while major issues remain unaddressed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Pareto principle applies: the largest bottleneck typically accounts for the majority of perceivable slowness, so fixing it yields the most impactful improvement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f5a453bf a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing animation and rendering performance" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Target 16ms per frame budget for 60fps animations. Use GPU-accelerated properties (transform, opacity) instead of layout-triggering properties (width, height, top, left)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Exceeding the 16ms frame budget causes visible jank. Layout-triggering CSS properties force costly reflows, while transform and opacity are handled by the compositor without layout recalculation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f5a8a1ef a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "At the start of every optimization engagement" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Gather Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID/INP, CLS), load time metrics, bundle size, runtime frame rate, and network waterfall before making any changes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Baseline metrics are essential to measure improvement and avoid optimizing things that don't actually matter." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

